        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued May 18 at 1:02PM CDT until May 18 at 1:15PM CDT by NWS Tulsa OK</headline>
        <description>At 101 PM CDT, a severe thunderstorm was located 4 miles northeast of
Cedarville, moving east at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Golf ball size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...People and animals outdoors will be injured. Expect damage
to roofs, siding, windows, and vehicles.

Locations in or near the path include...
Chester...                        Mountainburg...
Cedarville...                     Lee Creek...

This includes Interstate 49 between mile markers 24 and 33, and
between mile markers 36 and 39.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
